Hero Image Not Loading: The hero image for “Art Acquisition for New Collectors” isn’t loading on the dashboard or when accessing the guide through the “Read Guide” link.

Search Results Visibility: When I searched “I need a present for my wife for our silver anniversary,” the interface showed a “searching” message for about a minute. I initially thought the search was still running before realizing that clicking the field revealed the results. It might be helpful to show a few suggested options right away with a “see more” prompt that encourages users to expand the field for additional results.

Chat Error After Clarifying Question: In the chat panel, I was asked a follow-up question about whether I would like something that could be personalized or engraved. After responding that I’d like it to be personalized, the system returned what looks like a backend error message instead of continuing the conversation.

Text Visibility on Guides Page: On the page buy-anything.com/guides, the text colors make the content difficult to read. The header text only becomes visible when hovering over it, and the body text cannot be highlighted. If this is an intentional design feature to prompt interaction, it may still be a bit confusing from a usability standpoint.


Guide Content and Formatting: The guides didn’t seem to offer much actionable information. If these pages are still being built out, adding more detail or examples could make them more helpful. I also noticed that some formatting elements and images were not loading properly during my visit.

Vendor Directory Relevance: I searched “house cleaning in Denver,” but only one of the results listed was actually a house cleaning service. The other home-related options included services like window or carpet cleaning, and the remaining results were unrelated, such as a Denver bookstore, the Denver Art Museum, and Denver International Airport. I would expect the links in this directory to be more closely aligned with the search request.


Search Bar Results: I searched “I am looking for a vacation option for my family of adult children where we can relax in a remote setting yet still go out to eat in a nice restaurant each night.” The page returned many links but provided very little context or explanation for why they were recommended. Additionally, none of the “Request a Quote” buttons appeared to work.

